From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Martin Schmiedel <Martin.Schmiedel@tq-group.com>
Date: Mon, 5 May 2025 08:00:00 +0200
Subject: fix: IMX9 flash.bin via binman, not u-boot.cnt path

The main Makefile's CONFIG_SPL_LOAD_IMX_CONTAINER block tries to build
flash.bin via u-boot.cnt, but arch/arm/mach-imx has no u-boot.cnt rule
for IMX9 -- only for IMX8/IMX8M. This causes Error 2 at u-boot.cnt when
building for i.MX93.

For IMX9, the correct path is BINMAN: imx93-u-boot.dtsi contains a
complete descriptor that builds u-boot-spl-ddr.bin (SPL + DDR firmware),
spl.bin (ELE + SPL container), u-boot-container.bin (ATF + U-Boot
container), and assembles flash.bin from them.

Two-line fix:
1. Extend the CONFIG_SPL_LOAD_IMX_CONTAINER guard so it only covers
   non-IMX9 boards (by appending CONFIG_ARCH_IMX9 to the condition):
   "yy" != "y", so IMX9 falls through to the binman block.
2. In the binman block, add SPL as a conditional prerequisite for IMX9
   so that arch/arm/mach-imx's SPL target generates spl/u-boot-spl.cfgout
   and u-boot-container.cfgout before binman invokes mkimage.
---
 Makefile | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/Makefile b/Makefile
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -1512,7 +1512,7 @@ SPL: spl/u-boot-spl.bin FORCE
 	$(Q)$(MAKE) $(build)=arch/arm/mach-imx $@
 
 #ifeq ($(CONFIG_ARCH_IMX8M)$(CONFIG_ARCH_IMX8), y)
-ifeq ($(CONFIG_SPL_LOAD_IMX_CONTAINER), y)
+ifeq ($(CONFIG_SPL_LOAD_IMX_CONTAINER)$(CONFIG_ARCH_IMX9), y)
 u-boot.cnt: u-boot.bin FORCE
 	$(Q)$(MAKE) $(build)=arch/arm/mach-imx $@
 
@@ -1520,7 +1520,7 @@ flash.bin: spl/u-boot-spl.bin u-boot.cnt FORCE
 	$(Q)$(MAKE) $(build)=arch/arm/mach-imx $@
 else
 ifeq ($(CONFIG_BINMAN),y)
-flash.bin: spl/u-boot-spl.bin $(INPUTS-y) FORCE
+flash.bin: spl/u-boot-spl.bin $(if $(CONFIG_ARCH_IMX9),SPL) $(INPUTS-y) FORCE
 	$(call if_changed,binman)
 else
 flash.bin: spl/u-boot-spl.bin u-boot.itb FORCE
-- 
Armbian

